      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; standard simulation workflow review is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup was reviewed by a senior CFD engineer with 10+ years of cardiovascular device experience. No formal use-error assessment is required at MRL 2 for this factor."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; selection of turbulence and hemolysis constitutive models with literature justification is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model were selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pump CFD. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameter distributions for flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity must be documented and propagated through the model to characterize output uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Uncertainty quantification was performed using Monte Carlo sampling (n=500) over documented distributions for inlet flow rate (±5%, normal), rotational speed (±2%, normal), and blood analog viscosity (±8%, uniform). Output uncertainty in NIH was reported as 95th-percentile bounds. Note: identification of dominant input drivers via formal sensitivity analysis is planned for the next revision cycle and was not completed prior to this submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
